# Add New REST Endpoint — Procedure

One endpoint = one PR slice when possible. Read spec **before** code. Glob patterns → `14-backend-controllers.mdc`, `10-backend-general.mdc`; this how-to is the ordered checklist.

## Step 0: Preconditions

- [ ] Endpoint defined or updated in `docs/03_API_CONTRACTS.md` (path, method, auth, request/response, status codes).
- [ ] Domain rules in `docs/01_DOMAIN_MODEL.md` if new resource or state transition.
- [ ] DB change needed? → `@42-add-prisma-migration` first, then return here.
- [ ] New permission rule? → `@43-add-authorization-policy` in same PR.

Load: `docs/03_API_CONTRACTS.md` (relevant §), `docs/04_BACKEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm 2–3, `docs/07_SECURITY_IMPLEMENTATION.md` Bölüm 5.

## Step 1: Choose Module and Route

| Resource | Module path | Controller prefix |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Campaign | `apps/api/src/campaigns/` | `campaigns` |
| Character | `apps/api/src/characters/` | `characters` |
| Homebrew | `apps/api/src/homebrew/` | `homebrew` |
| Auth | `apps/api/src/auth/` | `auth` |
| Admin | `apps/api/src/admin/` | `admin` |

New resource type → new NestJS module per `docs/04_BACKEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm 1 ([CODE-003]). Register in `app.module.ts`.

Path: `/api/v1/<kebab-resource>` — global prefix in `main.ts`, controller uses relative path only.

## Step 2: DTO (Request Validation)

Create `create-*.dto.ts` / `update-*.dto.ts` in module `dto/` folder.

```typescript
// apps/api/src/campaigns/dto/create-campaign.dto.ts
import { IsString, IsOptional, MaxLength } from 'class-validator';

export class CreateCampaignDto {
  @IsString()
  @MaxLength(100)
  name: string;

  @IsOptional()
  @IsString()
  @MaxLength(2000)
  description?: string;
}
```

- Body/query: `class-validator` + global `ValidationPipe` (whitelist, forbidNonWhitelisted).
- Shared Zod for JSONB homebrew `data` → validate in **service** with `packages/shared` schema (`docs/04` Bölüm 7).
- List query: reuse `common/dto/list-query.dto.ts` — `limit` max 50, cursor pagination (`docs/03` Bölüm 1).

## Step 3: Controller (Thin)

```typescript
@Controller('campaigns')
export class CampaignsController {
  constructor(private readonly campaignsService: CampaignsService) {}

  @Post()
  @RequireVerifiedEmail()
  @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)
  create(@CurrentUser() user: AuthUser, @Body() dto: CreateCampaignDto) {
    return this.campaignsService.create(user, dto);
  }

  @Get(':id')
  findOne(@CurrentUser() user: AuthUser, @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string) {
    return this.campaignsService.findOne(id, user);
  }
}
```

Decorator checklist (`docs/04` Bölüm 4):

| Concern | Decorator |
| --- | --- |
| Public read | `@Public()` |
| Verified write | `@RequireVerifiedEmail()` |
| Admin only | `@Roles(Role.ADMIN)` |
| UUID param | `ParseUUIDPipe` |

**Never** put Prisma or policy `if` chains in controller.

## Step 4: Service (Business Logic + Policy)

```typescript
async findOne(id: string, user: AuthUser) {
  const campaign = await this.prisma.campaign.findUnique({
    where: { id },
    include: { members: true },
  });
  if (!campaign || !CampaignPolicy.canRead(user, campaign)) {
    throw new NotFoundException(); // 404 — no existence leak
  }
  return { data: campaign };
}
```

- Policy in `common/policies/` — `@43-add-authorization-policy`.
- 404 vs 403: unauthorized read → **404**; known resource, forbidden write → **403** (`docs/07` Bölüm 5.3).
- Response envelope: `{ data }` or list `{ data, nextCursor, hasMore }` (`docs/03` Bölüm 1).
- Errors: `{ statusCode, error, message, details? }` — `error` SCREAMING_SNAKE, `message` English.

## Step 5: Module Wiring

```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [PrismaModule],
  controllers: [CampaignsController],
  providers: [CampaignsService],
  exports: [CampaignsService],
})
export class CampaignsModule {}
```

Export service only if another module injects it (e.g. WebSocket broadcast).

## Step 6: Shared Types (if needed)

If FE needs new enums or response shapes → `packages/shared` first, then import in API and web. Single source ([CODE-002]).

## Step 7: Integration Tests (Mandatory for Auth)

Location: `apps/api/test/` or `*.controller.spec.ts` beside module.

Minimum matrix per `docs/08_TESTING_STRATEGY.md` Bölüm 5:

| Actor | Typical expectation |
| --- | --- |
| `owner` | 200/201 on own resource |
| `otherUser` | 404 (read) or 403 (write) |
| `unverified` | 403 on verified-only writes |
| `guest` | 401 |
| `ADMIN` | bypass where spec says |

```typescript
it('404 — non-member cannot read campaign', async () => {
  const res = await request(app.getHttpServer())
    .get(`/api/v1/campaigns/${campaign.id}`)
    .set(authHeader(strangerToken));
  expect(res.status).toBe(404);
});
```

Use `test/factories/` + `loginAsUser` (`docs/08` Bölüm 4). Real Postgres test DB.

## Step 8: Update API Contract Doc

If implementation diverged from spec → update `docs/03_API_CONTRACTS.md` **in same PR**:

- Method, path, auth column
- Request body fields
- Success response shape and status
- Error codes

## Step 9: Frontend Hook (if user-facing)

When endpoint is consumed by UI:

1. Add RTK Query endpoint in `apps/web/src/features/<domain>/*Api.ts` (`docs/05` Bölüm 5).
2. Tag invalidation for related lists.
3. Do **not** rely on FE for security — backend guard is source of truth.

## Step 10: Pre-PR Verification

```bash
pnpm lint
pnpm typecheck
pnpm --filter api test -- --ci
```

Checklist (`03-security-baseline.mdc`):

```
[ ] POST/PATCH/PUT/DELETE has guard + policy
[ ] Prisma only — no raw SQL
[ ] password_hash / refresh token not in response or logs
[ ] DTO validation on all inputs
[ ] Auth integration tests for permission matrix
[ ] docs/03 updated if contract changed
```

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Guard'sız write endpoint
- ❌ Controller with 20+ line permission logic
- ❌ Offset pagination (`?page=2`)
- ❌ Turkish `message` strings
- ❌ Copying full API tables into `.mdc` or code comments
- ❌ Integration tests skipped for new auth rules

## HTTP Status Quick Reference

| Case | Status | `error` example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Created | 201 | — |
| Success body | 200 | — |
| Delete success | 204 | no body |
| Validation | 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` |
| Unauthenticated | 401 | — |
| Email not verified | 403 | `EMAIL_NOT_VERIFIED` |
| Forbidden write | 403 | `FORBIDDEN` |
| Not found / unauthorized read | 404 | — |
| Conflict | 409 | `ALREADY_MEMBER` |
| Business rule | 422 | `LAST_ADMIN` |
| Rate limit | 429 | `TOO_MANY_REQUESTS` |

Full taxonomy → `docs/03_API_CONTRACTS.md` Bölüm 2.

## Nested and Admin Routes

| Pattern | Example |
| --- | --- |
| Sub-resource | `@Controller('campaigns/:campaignId/dm-notes')` |
| Action endpoint | `@Post(':id/invite/regenerate')` |
| Admin namespace | `@Controller('admin/users')` + `@Roles(Role.ADMIN)` |

Nested routes still delegate to service; load parent resource for policy chain.

## List Endpoints

```typescript
async findAll(user: AuthUser, query: ListQueryDto) {
  const limit = Math.min(query.limit ?? 20, 50);
  const items = await this.prisma.campaign.findMany({
    take: limit + 1,
    cursor: query.cursor ? { id: query.cursor } : undefined,
    where: this.buildListWhere(user),
    orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
  });
  const hasMore = items.length > limit;
  const data = hasMore ? items.slice(0, limit) : items;
  return {
    data,
    nextCursor: hasMore ? data[data.length - 1].id : null,
    hasMore,
  };
}
```

Filter/sort params per resource § in `docs/03`.

## Custom Business Exceptions

Use `common/exceptions/` for domain errors (`LastAdminException`, `InvalidInviteTokenException`). Map to envelope in filter — do not return raw strings.

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Check |
| --- | --- |
| 401 on all routes | `@Public()` missing on auth/reference reads |
| 403 EMAIL_NOT_VERIFIED | `@RequireVerifiedEmail()` on write |
| Validation strips fields | DTO missing decorator; `whitelist` drops unknown |
| 500 on JSONB | Zod `safeParse` in service before Prisma write |

## Decision Triggers

| Situation | Action |
| --- | --- |
| New framework or major library | `@45-write-architectural-decision` before coding |
| WebSocket side-effect on write | Also `@47-websocket-live-fields` |
| Faz work | Branch via `@48-git-phase-branch` |

